	  <td width="468" height="37" align="top" class="infoTD_text">
        <b>Directions from<strong> Points North                   thru Susanville, California:</strong></b>	  </td>
	</tr>
    <tr>
    <td class="infoTD_text">
    
   

<p>From midtown Susanville at Junction Hwy 139 & Hwy 36 take Hwy 36 West towards Chester. (Travel approx 23 miles). At Junction 147 turn left (South) towards Clear Creek. Go Â½ mile to stop sign, turn right stay on 147 thru Clear Creek. You continue toward Lake Almanor and will be driving along the East side of the Lake to Junction 89 (approx 10.8 miles). Turn left towards Greenville/Quincy. Travel thru Canyon Dam, Greenville, Crescent Mills, (approx 14 miles). After you drive thru Crescent Mills about 1mile, you will come to a sign that says Taylorsville/Arlington Rd, turn left over Railroad tracks towards Taylorsville.</p>

<p>In the town it is named Main Street as well. Stay on the road through town, past the Rodeo grounds on your left. At that point the road goes slightly to your right, follow that. If you stay right on Main/A22 you will be fine. Continue on A22 for approximately 6 miles through the trees. As you come into the valley you will see the buildings that make up the 'town' of Genesee and Genesee Home will be the first building on your right.</p>

<p>Genesee Home is approximately 6 miles east of Taylorsville. You will come into the valley and the town of Genesee will be the first set of buildings you come to. Genesee Home is the large red brick house on your right. Our driveway is just past the row of mail boxes on your right. If you go farther than 6 miles turn around for you have driven past Genesee Home.Come around to the front and we will meet you there. Please feel free to come right into GH no need to knock. You are Welcome.</p>


<p>Note if you are arriving in the dark, Genesee Home is approximately 6 miles east of Taylorsville. You will come into the valley and the first lights you see on your right will be Genesee Home. We will have the parking lot lights on for you. It is easy to miss the mail boxes at night. If you go farther than 6 miles, turn around.</p>

<p>PLEASE NOTE: THE FINAL DESTINATION, AS SHOWN ON MAP QUEST, INDICATES THE PROPERTY A MILE TO THE EAST OF ITS ACTUAL LOCATION. GENESEE HOME IS LOCATED IN THE TOWN OF GENESEE, WHICH IS SHOWN ON THE MAP DIRECTLY TO THE WEST OF THE "STARRED" LOCATION.</p>
    
